Package: tcos
Architecture: all
Depends: tcos-keyring, initramfs-tools-tcos (>= 0.84.5) , tcos-usplash (>= 0.84.5) [i386],
	 ${misc:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends},
         atftpd, dhcp3-server | dhcp-server, tcosmonitor, 
         openbsd-inetd | netkit-inetd | inetutils-inetd,
         aumix, pulseaudio, pulseaudio-utils, x11vnc, libasound2-plugins, xfs,
         mtools, ltspfs-server, esound, alsa-utils, cdebootstrap,
         shfs-utils, python, python-configobj, fuse-utils
Recommends: pulseaudio-esound-compat
Provides: tcos-server-utils
Replaces: tcos-server-utils
XB-Python-Version: ${python:Versions}
Description: new thin client implementation
 This is a system for generating thin client hosts using initramfs.
 TCOS is a set of build tools to prepare an initramfs image to boot
 thin client terminals.
 TCOS support dhcp, sound (alsa & esound | pulseaudio ), ltspfs, 
 Xorg (6.9 or 7.x) and more utils.
 .
 This metapackage will install all required packages to make a 
 thin client server.
 .
  Homepage: http://www.tcosproject.org
